SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYSunday 2 January S10 V1  Leeds United have an opportunity to turn their season around as they host Burnley in the English Premier League on Sunday. More details at www.soccer6.co.za M1 Bristol City vs Millwall: Millwall have won on their last two trips to Ashton Gate and before that forced three draws.M2 Blackburn Rovers v Huddersfield Town: Blackburn have won six games in a row but only one of their past six home games against Huddersfield.M3 Brentford vs Aston Villa: Brentford have won their last three home games against Villa, when both clubs were together in the Championship.M4 Everton vs Brighton & Hove Albion: Everton have six wins and two draws in their eight previous home games against Brighton.M5 Leeds United vs Burnley: Leeds have lost their last three games conceding 14 goals. Burnley have only won six times on 28 past trips to Elland Road, the last in 2013.M6 Southampton vs Newcastle United: Southampton have a single victory in their past eight outings. Newcastle have won one point from their past four matches.M7 Atletico Madrid vs Rayo Vallecano: Atletico Madrid vs Rayo Vallecano: Champions Atletico are seeking to stem a run of three successive defeats. Rayo have won three of their past four fixtures and sit in fourth place in La Liga, one point above Atletico.M8 Elche vs Granada: Granada have won three in a row over Elche, who are only above the La Liga relegation places on goal difference only.M9 Chelsea vs Liverpool: Chelsea have lost two of their last three home games against Liverpool.M10 Mallorca vs Barcelona: Barca have won seven in a row against Mallorca with a goal aggregate of 28-4. Suggested permutation: R8.00 2,3 x 1 x 2,3 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 3